11 AMENDMENT NO. 1. Strike the stricken title, enacting clause, and
entire bill and insert:
12
13 "An Act relating to 2-1-1 services; creating the 2-1-
1 Hotline Revolving Fund; specifying type of fund and
14 source of monies; stating purpose of the fund;
providing for expenditure of monies; providing for
15 codification; providing an effective date; and
declaring an emergency.
16
17
18 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
19 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
20 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 3022 of Title 56, unless there
21 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
22 A. There is hereby created in the State Treasury a revolving
23 fund for the Department of Human Services to be designated the “2-1-
24 1 Hotline Revolving Fund”. The fund shall be a continuing fund, not
ENGR. H. A. to ENGR. S. B. NO. 1290 Page 1

1 subj ect to fiscal year limitations, and shall consist of all monies
2 received by the Department from legislative appropriations provided
3 for the purpose of maintaining a robust 2-1-1 system in this state.
4 All monies accruing to the credit of the fund are hereby
5 appropriated and may be budgeted and expended by the Department for
6 the purpose provided for in this section. Expenditures from the
7 fund shall be made upon warrants issued by the State Treasurer
8 against claims filed as prescribed by law with the Director of the
9 Office of Management and Enterprise Services for approval and
10 payment.
11 B. No monies from the 2-1-1 Hotline Revolving Fund shall be
12 used to provide referrals, information, or assistance to any
13 organization, entity, or service that performs, promotes, or
14 facilitates abortions. Instead, the 2-1-1 system shall prioritize
15 referrals to crisis pregnancy centers, adoption agencies, and other
16 life-affirming resources that support expectant mothers and families
17 in choosing life. The Department of Human Services shall ensure
18 compliance with this subsection through annual audits and reporting
19 to the Legislature.
20 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
21 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
22 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
23 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
24 be in full force from and after its passage and approval."
