9 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
10 SECTION 4. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
11 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 3022 of Title 56, unless there
12 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
13 A. There is hereby created in the State Treasury a revolving
14 fund for the Department of Human Services to be designated the “2-1-
15 1 Hotline Revolving Fund”. The fund shall be a continuing fund, not
16 subject to fiscal year limitations, and shall consist of all monies
17 received by the Department from legislative appropriations provided
18 for the purpose of maintaining a robust 2-1-1 system in this state.
19 All monies accruing to the credit of the fund are hereby
20 appropriated and may be budgeted and expended by the Department for
21 the purpose provided for in this section. Expenditures from the
22 fund shall be made upon warrants issued by the State Treasurer
23 against claims filed as prescribed by law with the Director of the
24
ENGR. S. B. NO. 1290 Page 1

1 Offi ce of Management and Enterprise Services for approval and
2 payment.
3 B. No monies from the 2-1-1 Hotline Revolving Fund shall be
4 used to provide referrals, information, or assistance to any
5 organization, entity, or service that performs, promotes, or
6 facilitates abortions. Instead, the 2-1-1 system shall prioritize
7 referrals to crisis pregnancy centers, adoption agencies, and other
8 life-affirming resources that support expectant mothers and families
9 in choosing life. The Department of Human Services shall ensure
10 compliance with this subsection through annual audits and reporting
11 to the Legislature.
12 SECTION 5. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
13 SECTION 6. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
14 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
15 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
16 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
